This is Perl module Loop::Sustainable.

INSTALLATION

Loop::Sustainable installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is set up,
you should just be able to do

    % cpan Loop::Sustainable

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

Loop::Sustainable documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc Loop::Sustainable

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

